<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-26T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-26T13:00:00-05:00" n="128" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d128">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.142/2713</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-26T18:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">November
                                            26, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 27, 6.10
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>7815. For <persName corresp="#p_DHP1">Davison</persName>,<note n="1" xml:id="d128fn1"><persName corresp="#p_DHP1">Henry P.
                                        Davison</persName>, chairman of the War Council of the
                                    American Red Cross.</note> American Red Cross [from
                                    <persName>Endicott</persName><note n="2" xml:id="d128fn2">Lieut.
                                    Col. <persName>William Endicott</persName>, in charge of the
                                    American Red Cross Commission to Great Britain.</note>]:</p>
                            <p>1060. Blockade Department inform us practical embargo on all
                                shipments Britain to Russia. British Red Cross confirm this, stating
                                impossible ship opium which was to have left this week it being
                                impossible to ship earlier. Have consequently canceled purchases and
                                shall not draw.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_PW1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>